{#- outer_func wraps an inner inverse function of a fixed fraction `value`. The
    task is a deterministic transformation: simplify to a rational number using trig
    identities (half-angle formula when the inner angle is halved, otherwise the
    Pythagorean identity). Lookup tables produce clean LaTeX. -#}
{%- set outer = {'tg': '\\operatorname{tg}', 'ctg': '\\operatorname{ctg}'} -%}
{%- set arcname = {'1/2 * arccos': '\\arccos', 'arccos': '\\arccos', 'arcsin': '\\arcsin'} -%}
{%- set vals = {'3/5': '\\frac{3}{5}', '4/5': '\\frac{4}{5}', '5/13': '\\frac{5}{13}', '12/13': '\\frac{12}{13}'} -%}
{%- set halved = inner_func == '1/2 * arccos' -%}
MATH CONSTRAINTS (do not alter any number):
- Expression: y = {{ outer[outer_func] }}\left({{ '\\tfrac{1}{2}' if halved else '' }}{{ arcname[inner_func] }}{{ vals[value] }}\right)
- Task: simplify this to a single rational number, then confirm the sign of the result
  from the quarter in which the inner angle lies.
- Method to recall (do NOT reveal the result): {{
    'the inner angle is HALVED, so use the half-angle identity tg^2(a/2) = (1 - cos a)/(1 + cos a) (and its ctg counterpart), with cos a = ' ~ value
    if halved else
    'rewrite the outer function through sine and cosine of the inner angle, then use the Pythagorean identity sin^2 + cos^2 = 1 to get the missing ratio from ' ~ value }}.
- Watch the SIGN when taking the square root: it is fixed by the quarter of the angle,
  not chosen arbitrarily.
- Render all math as LaTeX inside $...$.
- Do NOT state or hint at the answer: the final numeric value and its sign must NOT be
  given to the student.
